trans-unit.source: Applies To: Azure AD Graph API
trans-unit.target: Applies To: Azure AD Graph API

trans-unit.source: This topic provides descriptions of the properties of the <system>Application</system> entity.
trans-unit.target: This topic provides descriptions of the properties of the <system>Application</system> entity.

trans-unit.source: Any application that outsources authentication to Azure AD must be registered in a directory.
trans-unit.target: Any application that outsources authentication to Azure AD must be registered in a directory.

trans-unit.source: This involves telling Azure AD about your application, including the URL where it’s located, the URL to send replies after authentication, the URI to identify your application, and more.
trans-unit.target: This involves telling Azure AD about your application, including the URL where it’s located, the URL to send replies after authentication, the URI to identify your application, and more.

trans-unit.source: For more information, see <legacyLink xlink:href="874839d9-6de6-43aa-9a5c-613b0c93247e#BKMK_Registering" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">Basics of Registering an Application in Azure AD</legacyLink>.
trans-unit.target: For more information, see <legacyLink xlink:href="874839d9-6de6-43aa-9a5c-613b0c93247e#BKMK_Registering" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">Basics of Registering an Application in Azure AD</legacyLink>.

trans-unit.source: <embeddedLabel>Namespace</embeddedLabel>: Microsoft.DirectoryServices for version 1.5 and newer, Microsoft.WindowsAzure.ActiveDirectory for versions prior to 1.5.
trans-unit.target: <embeddedLabel>Namespace</embeddedLabel>: Microsoft.DirectoryServices for version 1.5 and newer, Microsoft.WindowsAzure.ActiveDirectory for versions prior to 1.5.

trans-unit.source: The <system>Application</system> entity has the following properties:
trans-unit.target: The <system>Application</system> entity has the following properties:

trans-unit.source: The unique identifier for the application.
trans-unit.target: The unique identifier for the application.

trans-unit.source: The collection of application roles that an application may declare.
trans-unit.target: The collection of application roles that an application may declare.

trans-unit.source: These roles can be assigned to users, groups or service principals.
trans-unit.target: These roles can be assigned to users, groups or service principals.

trans-unit.source: <languageKeyword>true</languageKeyword> if the application is shared with other tenants; otherwise, <languageKeyword>false</languageKeyword>.
trans-unit.target: <languageKeyword>true</languageKeyword> if the application is shared with other tenants; otherwise, <languageKeyword>false</languageKeyword>.

trans-unit.source: The display name for the application.
trans-unit.target: The display name for the application.

trans-unit.source: A bitmask that configures the "groups" claim issued in a user or OAuth 2.0 access token that the application expects.
trans-unit.target: A bitmask that configures the "groups" claim issued in a user or OAuth 2.0 access token that the application expects.

trans-unit.source: The bitmask values are: 0: None, 1: Security groups and Azure AD roles, 2: Reserved, and 4: Reserved.
trans-unit.target: The bitmask values are: 0: None, 1: Security groups and Azure AD roles, 2: Reserved, and 4: Reserved.

trans-unit.source: Setting the bitmask to 7 will get all of the security groups, distribution groups, and Azure AD directory roles that the signed-in user is a member of.
trans-unit.target: Setting the bitmask to 7 will get all of the security groups, distribution groups, and Azure AD directory roles that the signed-in user is a member of.

trans-unit.source: The URL to the application’s homepage.
trans-unit.target: The URL to the application’s homepage.

trans-unit.source: The URIs that identify the application.
trans-unit.target: The URIs that identify the application.

trans-unit.source: For more information see, <legacyLink xlink:href="a09a6eb7-abf7-4d9d-8d8c-1d4c37a498e2" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">Application Objects and Service Principal Objects</legacyLink>.
trans-unit.target: For more information see, <legacyLink xlink:href="a09a6eb7-abf7-4d9d-8d8c-1d4c37a498e2" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">Application Objects and Service Principal Objects</legacyLink>.

trans-unit.source: The collection of key credentials associated with the application
trans-unit.target: The collection of key credentials associated with the application

trans-unit.source: Client applications that are tied to this resource application.
trans-unit.target: Client applications that are tied to this resource application.

trans-unit.source: Consent to any of the known client applications will result in implicit consent to the resource application through a combined consent dialog (showing the OAuth permission scopes required by the client and the resource).
trans-unit.target: Consent to any of the known client applications will result in implicit consent to the resource application through a combined consent dialog (showing the OAuth permission scopes required by the client and the resource).

trans-unit.source: The main logo for the application.
trans-unit.target: The main logo for the application.

trans-unit.source: Specifies whether this web application can request OAuth2.0 implicit flow tokens.
trans-unit.target: Specifies whether this web application can request OAuth2.0 implicit flow tokens.

trans-unit.source: Specifies whether, as part of OAuth 2.0 token requests, Azure AD will allow path matching of the redirect URI against the application's <system>replyUrls</system>.
trans-unit.target: Specifies whether, as part of OAuth 2.0 token requests, Azure AD will allow path matching of the redirect URI against the application's <system>replyUrls</system>.

trans-unit.source: The collection of OAuth 2.0 permission scopes that the web API (resource) application exposes to client applications.
trans-unit.target: The collection of OAuth 2.0 permission scopes that the web API (resource) application exposes to client applications.

trans-unit.source: These permission scopes may be granted to client applications during consent.
trans-unit.target: These permission scopes may be granted to client applications during consent.

trans-unit.source: Specifies whether, as part of OAuth 2.0 token requests, Azure AD will allow POST requests, as opposed to GET requests.
trans-unit.target: Specifies whether, as part of OAuth 2.0 token requests, Azure AD will allow POST requests, as opposed to GET requests.

trans-unit.source: The default is false, which specifies that only GET requests will be allowed.
trans-unit.target: The default is false, which specifies that only GET requests will be allowed.

trans-unit.source: The unique identifier for the application.
trans-unit.target: The unique identifier for the application.

trans-unit.source: A string that identifies the object type.
trans-unit.target: A string that identifies the object type.

trans-unit.source: For applications the value is always “Application”.
trans-unit.target: For applications the value is always “Application”.

trans-unit.source: The collection of password credentials associated with the application.
trans-unit.target: The collection of password credentials associated with the application.

trans-unit.source: Specifies whether this application is a public client (such as an installed application running on a mobile device).
trans-unit.target: Specifies whether this application is a public client (such as an installed application running on a mobile device).

trans-unit.source: Specifies the URLs that user tokens are sent to for sign in, or the redirect URIs that OAuth 2.0 authorization codes and access tokens are sent to.
trans-unit.target: Specifies the URLs that user tokens are sent to for sign in, or the redirect URIs that OAuth 2.0 authorization codes and access tokens are sent to.

trans-unit.source: Specifies resources that this application requires access to and the set of OAuth permission scopes and application roles that it needs under each of those resources.
trans-unit.target: Specifies resources that this application requires access to and the set of OAuth permission scopes and application roles that it needs under each of those resources.

trans-unit.source: This pre-configuration of required resource access drives the consent experience.
trans-unit.target: This pre-configuration of required resource access drives the consent experience.

trans-unit.source: The URL to the SAML metadata for the application.
trans-unit.target: The URL to the SAML metadata for the application.

trans-unit.source: The extension properties associated with the application.
trans-unit.target: The extension properties associated with the application.

trans-unit.source: Directory objects that are owners of the application.
trans-unit.target: Directory objects that are owners of the application.

trans-unit.source: The owners are a set of non-admin users who are allowed to modify this object.
trans-unit.target: The owners are a set of non-admin users who are allowed to modify this object.

trans-unit.source: <system>Application</system> also inherits other navigation properties from <link xlink:href="b0c66543-c74f-4e46-b617-76f9b780e99e" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">DirectoryObject</link>; however, none of these properties are valid for applications.
trans-unit.target: <system>Application</system> also inherits other navigation properties from <link xlink:href="b0c66543-c74f-4e46-b617-76f9b780e99e" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">DirectoryObject</link>; however, none of these properties are valid for applications.

trans-unit.source: If a request for any of these properties is sent, a <system>400 Bad Request</system> response is returned.
trans-unit.target: If a request for any of these properties is sent, a <system>400 Bad Request</system> response is returned.
